Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%16oz can}; pat very dry with #paper towels{}.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces (halve lengthwise first if carrots are on the larger side). Halve, peel, and slice @red onion{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges; mince a few wedges until you have 2 TBSP (4 TBSP for 4 servings). Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb} until you have 1 tsp (2 tsp for 4).

Toss chickpeas, carrots, and onion wedges on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{4%teaspoon}, @curry powder{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until chickpeas are crispy and veggies are tender, ~{18-22%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{4%teaspoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add ginger, half the minced onion, @garlic powder{3/4%tsp}, @garam masala{3/4%tsp}, and a big pinch of salt (for 4 servings, use 1 1/2 tsp garlic powder and 1 1/2 tsp garam masala.) (You'll use the rest of the garlic powder and garam masala later.) Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, @veggie stock concentrate{2}, and @water{3/4%cup} (1 1/2 cups for 4). Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low. Cover and cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with paper towels and season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{4%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

== Chutney ==

Mince @cilantro{1/4%ounce}; transfer to a #small bowl{}.

Add @red pepper jam{1}, remaining minced onion, remaining @garlic powder{1/4%tsp}, @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, and @white wine vinegar{1/2%tbsp} (2 TBSP olive oil and 1 TBSP vinegar for 4 servings) to bowl.

Stir to combine; season with salt and pepper.

> When adding the vinegar, be sure to measure it carefully - we sent more!

== Curry Sauce ==

In a second small bowl, combine @vegan mayonnaise{4%tablespoon}, remaining @garam masala{1/4%tsp}, @white wine vinegar{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings), and @sugar{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4).

Add @water{} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @peas{4%ounce} and a drizzle of @olive oil{4%teaspoon}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide rice and peas between #bowls{}; top with chickpeas and veggies. Drizzle with chutney and curry sauce. Serve.

When cool enough to handle, thinly slice chicken crosswise. Top rice and peas with chicken along with chickpeas and veggies.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.